<br>
If you give a wino a buck, he might use it to buy wine, or he might use it to eat.  Giving him that dollar doesn't encourage him to drink, he's gonna drink no matter what.  Giving him that dollar also doesn't risk your position in the lifeboat, it merely helps him tread water a little longer at no risk to yourself.<br>
<br>
His argument would work a lot better to address any form of communistic wealth sharing, but it doesn't work against a charity system that has very little impact on the giver. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=685611>KoT got me dis' stuff!</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hayzen>Hayzen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 771<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/03 6:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~digitalfoenix/nicholaswolfwood.JPG height=44 width=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We have no obligation to the world's needy.</span><hr size=1> Wolvar,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I don't see the relationship he is trying to prove between giving needed charity and &quot;encouraging overpopulation&quot;. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's pretty simple.  The poor countries are reproducing 41% faster than the comparatively rich countries.  The poor countries are starving due to this continuous increase in population.  Instead of getting their problem under control (i.e. stop being baby factories) some people propose we give them food.  But giving them food doesn't solve the problem, it just encourages them to keep having babies.  After all, why should they stop having babies as long as somebody else is supplying them with food?<br>
<br>
<br>
Likewise giving a wino money for alcohol doesn't do anything to help his problem. His problem is drinking, not with his lack of alcohol.  Giving him money to buy alcohol just gives him more incentive to continue drinking.  It just covers the problem up, or postpones it instead of him stopping drinking and actually solve his problem.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>that has very little impact on the giver.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Except it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>does</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> impact the giver.  As world population increases, world surplus decreases.  The rich nations will have less and less to give because the poor nations will consume more and more.<br>
<br>
The solution is to educate the poorer countries, not give them food and encourage them to have more babies. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolvar>Wolvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>My third character is Lovawr</span><br>  Posts: 2439<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/03 7:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We have no obligation to the world's needy.</span><hr size=1> Charity that is freely given NEVER unduly impacts the giver.<br>
