If people are starving, and you have a jar full of change sitting in your house collecting dust, wtf??  Sure it doesn't fix their problem, but it alleviates the symptoms.  <br>
<br>
Let's use the lifeboat analogy.  By your logic, (oh and i can't wait for you to post that this wasn't really your position cuz you didn't pick a side) we should hoard our life-preservers in the lifeboat because we might need them.  After all, the swimmers' problem isn't drowning, it's a lack of a lifeboat.  Since we can't give them a lifeboat, why toss them a life-preserver??<br>
<br>
When a world food bank contribution becomes mandatory for the people in the lifeboat, perhaps this foolish argument will make better sense.  Until then, it's fucking charity for starving people.   <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=685611>KoT got me dis' stuff!</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hayzen>Hayzen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 772<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/03 7:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~digitalfoenix/nicholaswolfwood.JPG height=44 width=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We have no obligation to the world's needy.</span><hr size=1> Wolvar,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Sure it doesn't fix their problem, but it alleviates the symptoms.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Okay, Wolvar, this is what is known as &quot;enabling&quot; and it is a bad thing to do because it only makes the problem worse, or at the very least does nothing to help solve it.<br>
<br>
Would you say the same thing about a crack addict? &quot;Well, giving him more crack isn't going to fix his problem, but at least he'll be relieved of his withdrawl sickness for a while.  So I'm helping!&quot;  Yeah, helping him stay a crack addict.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>When a world food bank contribution becomes mandatory for the people in the lifeboat, perhaps this foolish argument will make better sense. Until then, it's fucking charity for starving people. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think you need to revisit the &quot;Ruin of the Commons&quot; and &quot;World Food Bank&quot; part, because you obviously do not understand how it works.  The World Food Bank is not just for the starving nations. It is for the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>WORLD</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  It's for all of the nations that contribute to it.  It <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>isn't</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> charity.  It's a food reserve that is setup in case of emergencies that nations who have contributed to it can draw on when they need to.<br>
<br>
Say you and four friends decide to start a joint savings account &quot;just in case.&quot;  Three of your friends are relativley wealthy and well to do, but two of your friends are kind of lazy and don't work as hard as they could so they're less well to do.  All of you contribute to the joint savings account according to your abilities.  That means that you and your other two rich friends are putting in way more money than your two poor friends.  However, you all have decided that everyone should draw on the account according to their needs.  Obviously your two poorer friends will have greater needs than the three of you rich boys.  So continuously you three are putting in the bigger share of money, but your poor friends are drawing out the bigger share of money.<br>
<br>
Get it now? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hayzen>Hayzen</A> at: 9/17/03 7:42 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolvar>Wolvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>My third character is Lovawr</span><br>  Posts: 2442<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/03 7:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic&index=27>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We have no obligation to the world's needy.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Okay, Wolvar, this is what is known as &quot;enabling&quot; and it is a bad thing to do because it only makes the problem worse, or at the very least does nothing to help solve it.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
